olive oil
1 packet basmati rice
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
20 g butter
1 packet chicken breast strips
1 packet garlic paste
1 tin coconut milk
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 bag slaw mix
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet Crushed Peanuts
1 bag coriander
1 sachet Mild Caribbean Jerk Seasoning

• Boil the kettle. Half-fill a medium saucepan with boiling water.
• Add basmati rice and a pinch of salt. Cook, uncovered, over a high heat until tender, 12 minutes.
• Drain and return to saucepan. Add chicken-style stock powder and butter and stir to combine. Cover to keep warm.

• Meanwhile, heat a large frying pan over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• Cook chicken breast strips and 1/2 the mild Caribbean jerk seasoning until browned and cooked through, 3-4 minutes each side. Transfer to a bowl.

TIP: The spice blend will char slightly in the pan, this adds to the flavour!

• Return frying pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• Cook garlic paste until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add coconut milk and remaining jerk seasoning and simmer until slightly thickened, 2 minutes.
• Return chicken to the pan, stir to combine and season to taste

• Roughly chop baby spinach leaves.
• In a medium bowl combine baby spinach, slaw mix, white wine vinegar and a drizzle of olive oil.
• Divide rapid rice, creamy coconut Caribbean chicken and rainbow slaw between bowls.
• Top with crushed peanuts and serve with torn coriander.